					</outline>
				<outline text="iPhone day arrives" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 05:04:25 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/662288946/&quot;&gt;Big news from Palo Alto&lt;/a&gt;. A UPS truck pulls up at the Apple Store. Does it contain the iPhones. No one knows for sure!" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:17:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's fun to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/stories/2007/06/28/waitInLineWithoutWaitingIn.html&quot;&gt;watch&lt;/a&gt; the play by play!" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:18:47 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Everybody please remember, it's just a phone, okay?" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:20:21 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="uncov reviews Pownce" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:25:27 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I love these &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.uncov.com/2007/6/29/kevin-rose-you-are-doing-it-wrong&quot;&gt;guys&lt;/a&gt; whoever they are." created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:25:33 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&quot;Pownce also feels a little bit like Twitter except that its user interface makes you want to gouge your eyeballs out with a fork.&quot;" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:25:39 GMT"/>
					<outline text="They also point out that it's a lot like FTP, and is an overpriced repackaging of Amazon S3. And that the size limits prevent you from sharing anything really useful." created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:28:01 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="ISPs from the AOL era" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:44:25 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Quickly, I thought this morning I'd install the Comcast self-install network interface that arrived via UPS yesterday. Well, the first part went quickly, I got connected, but then it wanted me to download an installation kit, which once downloaded on my Mac (it came in as an hqx, so they clearly understood it was a Mac) wouldn't run because it required Internet Explorer. I imagine that's a big support headache for them. " created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:44:31 GMT"/>
					<outline text="No problem for me, I just launched Parallels, but it couldn't find the cable modem, so I'm stuck, which is probably okay, because I don't really want to install anything to get my second ISP connection in the house. I have six computers, so only one is going to get anything installed on it. And the clue that I didn't want to do it was the requirement that you disable all anti-virus software. Uh huh. Yeah, and why exactly should I do &lt;i&gt;that?&lt;/i&gt;" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:48:12 GMT"/>
					<outline text="They also require that you get a comcast.net mail address." created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:47:42 GMT"/>
					<outline text="When do you think buying Internet connectivity will get you that and only that." created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 16:48:32 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.wordpress.com/2007/06/29/scripting-news-for-6292007/#comment-84800&quot;&gt;Don Cook&lt;/a&gt;, a Mac user, called Comcast, they set it up on their end, and that was that. I figured that's all we had to do. I'll call them tomorrow." created="Fri, 29 Jun 2007 19:10:56 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
