					</outline>
				<outline text="Since we're into puzzles today" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 01:12:23 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uma_Thurman&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2007/06/27/uma.gif&quot; width=&quot;65&quot; height=&quot;217&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named uma.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.broadbandmechanics.com/2007/06/pageflakes-now-a-social-network&quot;&gt;Marc Canter&lt;/a&gt; and many other people think I'm full of it when I say the right number of identity systems for each user is 1. But I am right. And I know it." created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 01:12:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's a Zen puzzle, almost a riddle, one which a smart user like my pal &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/stories/2007/06/27/sheNailsIt.html&quot;&gt;Ponzi&lt;/a&gt; would never be confused by. You have to be a great geek tech genius like Marc to get it wrong. &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 01:12:55 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the puzzle. If all identity systems you use interoperate seamlessly, grasshopper, how many identity systems do you use?" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 01:11:46 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's a hint. How many email systems do you use? RSS systems? Web systems? The correct answers are 1, 1, and 1." created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 01:16:10 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The meme spreads nicely" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 00:26:05 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.webware.com/8301-1_109-9736178-2.html&quot;&gt;Rafe&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Pownce an interesting alternative to Twittergram.&quot;" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 00:26:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And everyone is invited to use Twittergram. &lt;i&gt;If you dare!&lt;/i&gt; &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2007 00:27:29 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Tinyurl has an API" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 18:16:06 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Of course I'd like to do what Twitter does, and generate a Tinyurl in place of a longish URL for each TwitterGram. I had assumed all along that Twitter had a special deal with the TInyurl folks, but apparently not so. They have an open API that is simplicity itself. It's so simple it's almost hard to describe." created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 18:16:11 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Try clicking on this link: " created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 18:17:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="http://tinyurl.com/api-create.php?url=http://scripting.com/ " created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 18:18:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It returns a Tinyurl. Copy it to the clipboard, and paste it into the address bar of your browser. it should take you to the home page of my weblog. Apparently it works for any URL you give it. And of course you can call it from a &lt;a href=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2007/06/27/tinyUrl.create.gif&quot;&gt;script&lt;/a&gt; just as easily as you click a link in a browser. &lt;i&gt;Very nice!&lt;/i&gt;" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 18:18:52 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I'm going to put this into twittergram.com, posthaste." created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 18:19:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: It's in, and it &lt;a href=&quot;http://twitter.com/twitogram/statuses/123426962&quot;&gt;works&lt;/a&gt;. &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 18:34:13 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="She nails it" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 17:24:17 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://twitter.com/ponzarelli/statuses/123326072&quot;&gt;Ponzi&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;How do we decide how many social networks is enough? Are there any central tools that can load all our info for us into multiple sites?&quot;" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 17:24:21 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The answer to the first question, imho, is: 1." created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 17:24:45 GMT"/>
					<outline text="To the second, no, not until we know which one is the answer to the first question." created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 17:25:09 GMT"/>
					<outline text="White man speak with forked tongue! &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 17:25:28 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/stories/2007/06/26/wereGettingClose.html&quot;&gt;Yesterday's post&lt;/a&gt; on identity is required to understand my answers here." created="Wed, 27 Jun 2007 20:49:51 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
