					</outline>
				<outline text="Just saw an iPhone ad on CNN" created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:25:05 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/543002213/&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1307/543002213_a228c96b1d_o.jpg&quot; width=&quot;105&quot; height=&quot;189&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;And it's good. Really good." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:25:15 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's how it goes..." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:25:21 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Narrator: &quot;You're watching Pirates of the Caribbean (on AppleTV of course), and someone says they'd like calimari.&quot;" created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:25:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The user clicks a button. Google Maps comes up. Click. A keyboard comes up. Types C-A-L-A-M-A-R-I. Enter." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:25:41 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Pushpins appear on the map. (The phone knows where you are?)" created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:26:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The user touches a pin. A small card with a phone number pops up. Clicks the number. The phone dials. Hello, please send over some calamari." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:26:44 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It's a subset of the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3WdS4TscWH8&amp;eurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Egoogle%2Ecom%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dknowledge%2Bnavigator%26ie%3Dutf%2D8%26oe%3Dutf%2D8%26aq%3Dt%26rls%3Dorg%2Emozilla%3Aen%2DUS%3Aoffi&quot;&gt;Knowledge Navigator&lt;/a&gt; without the &lt;a href=&quot;http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1262/543014293_6902aace7d_o.jpg&quot;&gt;guy&lt;/a&gt; in the bow tie." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:27:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Quite compelling. My Blackberry can't do it. Okay maybe I just decided to buy one." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:27:37 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Ooops. &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:27:56 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.wordpress.com/2007/06/12/scripting-news-for-6122007/#comment-74787&quot;&gt;Rich Karpinski says&lt;/a&gt; my Blackberry can do it, and iPhone doesn't have GPS. At least it's a good ad." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 21:54:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PPS: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apple.com/iphone/ads/ad3/&quot;&gt;The ad&lt;/a&gt; is on the Apple site, along with &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apple.com/iphone/ads/&quot;&gt;all the others&lt;/a&gt;." created="Tue, 12 Jun 2007 23:04:21 GMT"/>
